description:
goDeskless is a cloud-based workforce automation platform specially designed for the "deskless workforce" - your frontline field champions that interface with your customers and prospects.
 
The deskless workers often work in disconnected mode, and depend on the office-based CRM users for critical customer information. Lack of access to right information creates operational inefficiencies. The dependency on CRM creates customer experience friction with the three-way communication challenges between the customer, the CRM user, and the deskless worker, and results into significant revenue loss.
 
We solve these challenges by automating enterprise field operations in disconnected mode so the deskless workers always have access to local data to function regardless of connectivity, and using AI to connect consumers to the deskless workers without CRM intervention or dependency.  
 
Our AI-powered OnDemand Service Platform transforms enterprise data into Fast Data, and combines it with engaging experience. This allows workers to better utilize information and consistently achieve higher efficiencies in deskless mode.
 
We sell white-label ready smart-apps designed to work on smart phones and tablets for both consumers, as well as deskless workers.  We provide a consumer facing app for our customers' end users, and a field workforce management app for our customers' field workers.
 
The consumers request service through our app, and are automatically connected with the best available deskless worker. The consumer engages directly with the deskless worker while the CRM user takes a back seat and monitors. This experience is similar to the popular shared economy platforms that automate OnDemand Service Delivery (food, appliance, travel, etc).
 
We charge per monthly active user per month that connects to our platform. We monetize by selling our platform through Retail (Direct sale to enterprises), Wholesale (via resellers/partners), and White-l
tagLine: Remote, Secure Customer Engagement Platform for the Distributed Deskless Workforce
specialisation: Customer Service CRM, Enterprise SaaS, Customer Experience, In-App Customer Engagement, Digital Transformation, Mobile Self-Service, Field Service et Workforce Automation

description:
Founded in April 2013 and based in Potsdam near Berlin, Germany, Snaptrust specializes in the creation, recognition and verification of anti-counterfeiting markers. Backed by years of experience in image processing on mobile devices, company founder and general manager Cüneyt Göktekin has invented and patented more than 17 products and systems. One of the unique features of Snaptrust technology is that it is invisible to the human eye and can be detected/authenticated using a smartphone.

The Snaptrust marker can be applied on a variety of products without special machinery or production line modifications. This makes the technology cost-effective and easy to integrate into existing systems. No need for additional coatings or printing plates. The marker can be conveniently uploaded to designated production sites via Internet.

 

Authenticity is verified via smartphone. This keeps the tamper-proof marking confidential and eliminates the need to reveal it to line employees.

The patented Snaptrust system uses micro­scopic markers applied on the product surface. Complex interpolation and image processing algorithms recognize and verify these markers. This makes it possible to conceal several bytes of data (serial numbers, product information, etc.) in a single marker. Recognition and authentication takes place in real time on an offline mobile device. 

Snaptrust technology can be implemented across many different industries, from luxury goods and cosmetics, to tobacco and replacement parts.

Snaptrust is licensing it's technology to leading international brand owners.
    Friedrich-Ebert-Str. 84,  Potsdam, Brandenburg 14467, DE
specialisation: mobile real time imaging and recognition et mobile anti-counterfeiting

SEC Rules 17a-3 & 17a-4, Rule 204-2 of the US Investment Advisers Act and FINRA Rule 4511 require all written business-related communications, including email, instant messaging, Bloomberg, Thomson Reuters, text messaging, Twitter, Facebook, LinkedIn, Instagram and all other social media to be retained for record retention purposes for all employees.  

Only txtsmarter has resolved this huge problem, capturing and syncing data using native SMS applications into platforms protecting regulated industries fully while guarding against spoliation and federal agency compliance infractions. 

Over 18.7 billion text messages are sent daily, not including app-to-app messaging. 

We offer a solution that provides unprecedented capabilities to support monitoring, rules application and pre/post-incident reporting.

description:
The transition to a file-based workflow improves efficiency whilst simultaneously cutting down costs. Emotion Systems provides signal processing solutions for file-based workflows. Our product focus is efficiency, ease of use and engineering excellence. The products support a wide range of video and audio files (MXF, P2, LXF, QuickTime, WAV, AIFF and DPP; files with Dolby E ). 

eFF provides audio loudness compliance to a vast range of worldwide standards and can be used in multiple workflows including standalone, automatic watch folder and fully automatic through API integration.

Engine allows Automated File Based Audio workflows for Loudness, Dolby E Encoding and Decoding, Track mapping, replication and mute, Up mix, Down mix, language tagging and more. It is controlled by use of a ReSTful API and offers easy integration to popular MAM Systems.

Sky, Ericsson, NHK, Turner, Smoke & Mirrors, The Mill, Encompass, Arqiva, Globecast and AMC make up just part of Emotion Systems expanding worldwide customer base.

Playout, Broadcast and Post Production all reply on Emotion Systems for file-based audio processing and automated workflows. Emotion Systems specialises in the research and development of file-based signal processing products, with emphasis on software solutions that address the need for audio measurement and compliance. From normalizing files for playout to loudness compliance to Dolby encoding, automated audio processing  is saving time and money. Engine and Eff solve requirements for content prep, distribution, and delivery. Repetitive and impossible tasks don’t need to tie up the editorial staff and equipment. Automate repetitive tasks and let people be creative again! Here are some of the key areas we work in:

•	Loudness correction and compliance
•	Change QT moov or MXF stream structures from 1/O streams, to stereo streams, or to interleaved streams, or any mix needed 
•	Add language and channel layout meta data into a file
•	New file wrapping option - combines any number of MOV and WAV files and create new MXF files
•	New pitch adjustment module adjusts the duration of audio without changing the pitch from the original. Excellent when doing standards conversions between American and European frame rates


    London Road, Astor House, Newbury Business Park, Newbury, Berkshire RG14 2PZ, GB
tagLine: Automated File Based Audio Processing

description:
TeraDact Solutions, headquartered in Missoula, Montana with offices in Washington, DC and Edmonton, Alberta provides patented information management technology to identify, tag and remove information, manually or automatically according to user-defined rules. TeraDact’s capabilities ensures the privacy and security of sensitive information including data residing in the cloud, unstructured data, freeform text inside documents and underlying metadata with an audit function that provides access control and logging.

TeraDact allows for intelligent sharing of different versions of the same document. Operating in a collaborative environment, TeraDact can share a single document to multiple users at different access levels allowing users to only see and manipulate the information they are authorized to access. As users finish their review and save their work, TeraDact saves and stores only one complete version of the document simplifying version control and reducing the risk of data loss. 

TeraDact can facilitate the rapid flow of information throughout an enterprise while reducing staffing costs and storage requirements, accelerating operational decision-making, ensuring accurate and timely dissemination of data to those with a need to know.

TeraDact's proven capabilities extend to deep semantic search and Big Data / Cyber security analytics.  Resulting in significant added value to those tools and the intelligence of the knowledge bases they generate.

description:
ECaTS is an acronym for Emergency Call Tracking System. ECaTS is the first universal 911 Call Reporting System that leverages the ubiquitous nature of the Internet to provide secure, real-time reporting to the 911 industry.

ECaTS was originally developed by Direct Technology, a custom software development and hosting company back in 1997. Originally, the service was developed to solve a critical business need for the 911 Program Office in the State of California. The Program Office was seeking a solution that could provide universal 911 Call Statistics Analysis across the entire State, regardless of the type of Customer Premise Equipment (CPE) installed at each Public Safety Answering Point (PSAP). 

Direct Technology decided to accept the challenge. They developed and deployed the first version of the service in late 1997 and the result was an overwhelming success. ECaTS was the first service to abstract the complexity of collecting, reporting and managing 911 Call Statistics using a web browser and some creative technology.

The ECaTS MIS service has since been successfully deployed in a myriad of States and Counties. Its new version of the service embraces solid Business Intelligence and Collaboration features that are increasing the demand for the company's services across the industry. Thee ECaTS portfolio of services has grown to include Text To 911 reporting, Dashboard Monitor & Response, Data Migration, and Wireless Routing Analysis
    3009 Douglas Blvd., Suite 300, Roseville, California 95661, US
specialisation: SaaS, Data Analytics, Custom Software Development, Customer Servcie, Integration, Historical Importing, Public Safety Information Analytics, Call Detail Record Collection, 911 Wireless Routing Auditing, Text to 911 Reporting, Custom Reporting et Real-time Reporting

description:
Mission
================== 
Vana Learning's mission is to help academic coaches and tutors work quicker, efficiently manage their student data, and harness data analytics to deliver superior results for their students. 

About
=================
Founded in 2017 and based in Nashville, Tennessee, Vana began as a technologically enhanced, web-based K-12 classroom intervention. Based on existing evidence-based interventions, we helped make them both easier and more effective. 

Our K-12 intervention solution is undergoing a multi-year pilot, for which we are still accepting schools (pilot schools receive the product at no cost for three months). 

Our core product is our Coaching Management Platform. 

The Team

description:
Determining accurate cost basis has traditionally been a frustrating challenge for investors, tax professionals, advisors and institutions alike. Trying to identify and account for corporate actions that affect cost basis can take hours, days or even longer, depending on the complexity surrounding a security and the length of the holding period. Fortunately, there’s an easier solution – NetBasis. 

NetBasis provides accurate adjusted cost basis information in seconds. Drawing on a securities database extending back as far as 1925, it instantly accounts for historical pricing changes caused by stock splits, corporate mergers, dividend reinvestments and other events. 

With the enactment of strict new reporting regulations, cost basis accuracy has never been more important. Whether you’re looking to prepare Schedule D forms, calculate adjusted cost basis for 1099 reporting, determine the adjusted cost basis of inherited or gifted securities, or verify capital gains taxes, you’ll appreciate the precision – and efficiency – of NetBasis. It’s the same technology the IRS used to audit capital gains returns for its 2005 Tax Gap Report.

description:
Simplifying & Automating Security Configuration Mgmt

Businesses want to take advantage of the flexibility, scalability, and speed of the cloud. However, lack of proactive and automated processes for cloud management can lead to challenges such as increased costs, higher residual risk, and the impediment of DevOps. By delivering consistent security and compliance across cloud environments, Cloud Raxak enables businesses to undergo successful cloud transformations while reducing the risk, time, and costs involved.

Some key issues of cloud security are:
-- Security compliance is up to 40% of the cost of managing cloud applications
-- Manual or semi-automated security management is slow, error prone, and insecure
-- 50% of public cloud VM security parameters are configured incorrectly at boot
-- 95% of public cloud VM security parameters can be configured automatically, significantly reducing the time, costs, and human error involved

Raxak Protect is a SaaS-based security offering that empowers IT and application development teams, by simplifying and automating security and compliance across private and public clouds. Key features of the platform include:
-- Leading edge security profiles based on government and industry standards (CIS, DISA & NIST STIGs, PCI-DSS, HIPAA, FFIEC, FISMA, etc.)
-- Automatic integration and application of security profiles, so that cloud apps can be deployed quickly, cost-effectively, and without human error
-- Application of security profiles across clouds, enabling consistent and continuous protection
-- One-touch security compliance through IT service catalog tools like HP Cloud Service Automation, enabling both skilled and novice users to protect enterprise data
-- Integration into DevOps, enabling flexible security throughout application lifecycles 

For more information, please email us at info@cloudraxak.com, or visit our website and download our free guide to Securing Applications in the Cloud: https://www.cloudraxak.com/resource/
    1484 Pollard Rd #363,  Los Gatos, CA 95032, US

description:
Transitive Corporation (an IBM company) is a leader in cross-platform virtualization, and its award-winning technology is built into more than 17 million computers worldwide. Transitive's solutions allow software applications that have been compiled for one processor and operating system to run on systems with different processors and operating systems, without any source code or binary changes and at speeds comparable to native ports.

As a result, cross-platform virtualization allows IT managers to quickly and easily replicate legacy enterprise applications from the original hardware and run them on modern, standardized platforms without incurring the costs and delays of porting projects, and without disruption to end users. This workload replication helps enterprise customers improve business continuity, including superior disaster recovery, scalability and high-availability solutions.

Transitive’s cross-platform virtualization technology is the foundation for Apple’s Rosetta translation software (built into Apple’s Intel-based Macintosh computers) and also for PowerVM Lx86, which is available for IBM Power Systems enterprise servers. Transitive Corporation is located in Los Gatos, California with a research and development team in Manchester, UK.

description:
Powerful applicant tracking, provisioning, on-boarding, and auditing made simple.

Do any of these sound familiar?

Case Study 'A'
Today is Larry's first day on the job. "Where is his computer," you ask the IT guy. "Who? I didn't know we had a new employee starting today." Larry spends the first week on the job without a computer. Meanwhile he seriously reconsiders his decision to join the company.

Case Study 'B'
Joe terminates his employment with your company and accepts a job at a competitor. Months later you find out that he's been able to access your company's sensitive data. "Why does he still have access to our systems?" you ask the IT department. "Doesn't he still work here? Nobody told us to remove his access," they reply.

Case Study 'C'
"How come Bob, our part-time landscaping intern, drives a company-paid BMW? And why does he have a corporate credit card? Why does he have 16 Blackberries? Who authorized all of this!?!" (Situation exaggerated for dramatic effect.)

If any of these happen to your company, you owe it to yourself to give Resource Wagon a try. Resource Wagon replaces those well-intentioned clipboards and post-it notes with automated, auditable business processes. Say goodbye to the chaos, and say hello to timely resource acquisitions and revocations.

description:
KnoxMediaHub (KMH) is a SaaS Cloud Platform specifically built for the Media and Entertainment (M&E) Industry. 
Our Vision is that the Global M&E Industry will be completely Cloud-based by 2025. Players who fail to integrate the Cloud as the foundation of their businesses will disappear from the market.

Why is Cloud SaaS becoming critical for the M&E Industry?
Because Production and Post-production Studios and Distribution Platforms face increasing challenges to remain viable in the Digital Age. Two of these challenges are:
Complexity: operating in this Industry is becoming more and more complex, as Content must be produced and simultaneously delivered in multiple standards and definitions on all sorts of devices. More complexity means more cost if nothing else changes.
Decreasing Margins: the value-chain of the Industry is losing the "fat" of the old times, due to fundamental changes in the Industry structure and to the disruptive impact of Digital and the Internet, which enable new Busines Models quickly replacing old ones. And, it's just the beginning.
These two challenges are opposed to each other and represent a lethal mismatch that needs to be addressed at a Strategic level by established Companies.

How does KMH help Companies face such challenges and succeed?
By bringing Cloud-based SaaS Video Solutions to them and making them extremely easy to embrace. With them, Clients dramatically improve their Business by increasing Sales, Quality of Service and Margins by reducing Opex and Capex. KMH takes care of all operations and executes them unmanned where resources are unlimited and (orders of magnitude) more affordable. This simplifies our Clients' organizations and lets them become leaner.
KMH connects the industry in a collaborative space where content does not need to move but can be processed, edited, encoded and then exchanged with any global destination.

Contact us: we can get you started in minutes.
    Carrer de Benet Mateu, 40,  Barcelona, Cataluña 08034, ES
tagLine: Dispatch whatever you need whenever you want from wherever you are
specialisation: Cloud, Video Content, Media, Internet, Transcoding, Video Ingest, Video Delivery, Media Hub, Metadata, Media Asset Management et SaaS

description:
OR Technologies develops world leading technology for the built environment. Our core product offering is Organic Response - a Distributed Intelligence lighting control system that allows each individual luminaire to make lighting decisions based on the presence of occupants in its immediate vicinity, ambient light levels, and information it receives from its neighbouring luminaires. It then contributes information back to the luminaire community, so other luminaires can also make more informed lighting decisions. 

Although they make decisions individually, Distributed Intelligence means all the lights in a defined space act as a coordinated whole.  The result is a highly flexible, energy efficient lighting control system with a compelling proposition to developers, building owners and tenants:

* Organic Response is easy to install.  Because the control technology is integrated into light fittings before delivery to the building site, installation is as easy as installing a luminaire.  The system is completely Plug & Play, with no additional wiring or commissioning required for the system to operate.

* Once installed, the system is simple to operate, with various control parameters adjustable using a simple smartphone app.

* Organic Response has a rich feature set, delivering highly sophisticated lighting control through motion detection, daylight dimming, and scenes and zones functionality, amongst many others.

* The system has been independently evaluated in multiple installations, showing energy savings of between 56% -78%.
    2 Greenwood Street, Abbotsford, Melbourne, Victoria 3067, AU

We combine algorithms, natural language processing, phonetic similarity, and advanced search techniques to rate, rank, and visualize names that are the same or similar to yours — which could prevent you from building the brand you want.

A pioneer in professional name creation, SB is known for her creative and strategic naming and brand architecture innovations; for the famous names her companies create; and most recently for her software spin-off, Naming Matters.

Finding an ownable, defensible, and attractive name for a new company or product is always a challenge, a high-stake process for founders, investors, creative agencies, and enterprises. Creating names and evaluating them for availability (including the risk of being sued) has long remained the realm of founders struggling to do it themselves, creative agencies who do naming but not as their focus, and attorneys and branding consultants. Naming Matters aims to solve for this, a process that has barely changed in decades.

Naming Matters automates expert naming and branding services, making name creation and decision-making instant, inexpensive, and accessible to everyone, everywhere, including for agencies, enterprises, law firms, and entrepreneurs. Our natural language processing for trademark class matching (over 14 million trademarks assessed), combined with our proprietary algorithmic scoring, allows us to visualize trademark availability vs. risk. Together these allow users with no knowledge of how trademarks work to eliminate their risky names, and quickly focus on their best name candidates.

At SB’s naming company Master-McNeil, she has been responsible for creating Concur, PayPal, Clarium, Affirm, Eos, Ariba, Borealis, Connexant, Quid, Schwab Signature, Netopia, Planet Labs, Athlon, Duron, Opteron, and Sempron (for AMD), over 60 Apple names, Pixo, LaCrosse, OneWorld, Navigant, Rendezvous, and hundreds more.

description:
Bring people together for a sustainable work environment 

During his 20 years deploying smart building and workplace technologies for global clients, Fabien Girerd identified an unfulfilled need for a wireless, low-maintenance, integrated solution connected to the building operating systems to provide an intuitive experience.  

In 2014, Fabien started Jooxter in France to help clients manage flex desks and meeting rooms through wireless monitoring. The next natural iteration was to launch Live Occupancy®,  Jooxter’s smart occupancy solution and an enterprise grade digital platform collecting live office occupancy data agnostically. Jooxter’s solution provides valuable insights to clients who are making data-informed decisions to optimize their office space. Over the years, Fabien built a diverse team to serve clients internationally leading Jooxter to be an award-winning start up in the Smart Building and a recognized expert in the PropTech sector in 2021.

As the pandemic accelerated the workplace paradigm shift, our team leveraged its ingenuity and agility to design new digital experiences.  Jooxter is helping existing and new clients to navigate the hybrid work model challenges by creating reliable, flexible and scalable digital workplace solutions.  

Jooxter is more than ever focused on its vision to bring people together by taking a holistic approach to digital workplace to deliver key business outcomes.  To its clients, Jooxter is a strategic partner to enable collaboration, understand office occupancy and facilitate the use and management of the best suited workspaces for employees and leaders. 

Together with partners, we are creating an ecosystem to make your workplace smarter, every day.

5 more games launched in 2015: "Super Monster Mayhem: Rampage"​ , "Super Block Jumper"​ , "Cannon Land"​, "Twin Shooter Invaders"​ and "Age of Lords"​ , that  reached over 3 million downloads.

eRepublik Labs received the “GameLab most innovative games company award in 2015"​ and "Twin Shooter Invaders"​ won several industry recognitions including a Pocket Gamer Silver Award.

Veicoli nasce un paio di anni fa come progetto creato da 4 studenti dell’università degli studi di  Torino, diventato successivamente startup incubata presso “I3P-Incubatore Imprese Innovative del Politecnico di Torino” e tuttora una società costituita nel mese di Novembre 2014. Stiamo sviluppando due prodotti legati alla gestione dei mezzi su ruota: Veicoliapp e Veicoli for Business.

Il nostro principale prodotto è Veicoliapp, un’app web e mobile che si occupa della gestione di: scadenze, costi, manutenzioni, tagliandi, cambio degli pneumatici, note, rifornimenti, consumi e molte altre funzioni inerenti a tutti i mezzi circolanti su strada. Abbiamo più di 40.000 utenti iscritti, di cui il 78% sono utenti attivi e usano il servizio. Il nostro punto di forza è la gestione sincronizzata tra piattaforma web, android e ios dell’utente: tramite un singolo account, l’utente può accedere da smartphone o web al suo profilo in quanto i dati non sono memorizzati sui dispositivi mobile ma sul server in cloud. Quest’ultima è stata una nostra scelta fin dall’inizio per garantire la sicurezza e l’integrità dei dati dei nostri utenti.

Il nostro secondo prodotto è Veicoli for Business (online da pochi mesi), una piattaforma web dedicata esclusivamente ai professionisti di settore (centri revisione, officine, carrozzieri ed altri professionisti) tramite la quale il professionista può gestire i propri clienti, avvisarli nel momento in cui voglia effettuare delle promozioni tramite notifica push, email ed sms e sostituire completamente il sistema di avviso in prossimità di scadenze, fatto oggi in forma manuale e cartacea: il prodotto avviserà in modo automatico, tramite un algoritmo proprietario, i clienti del professionista tramite email e notifica push (per chi userà Veicoliapp) andando ad automatizzare il processo (il 90% dei professionisti spedisce ancora a mano la lettera per avvisare il cliente al momento della revisione) e andando così a ridurre lo spreco di carta e tempo

description:
Universities, global research organizations, and big corporations have people outside their core group of enterprise users that need access to online services.

Managing these external user accounts is costly to the enterprise and frustrating for the end user. That is where Cirrus Identity comes in. We make secure, easy to integrate, cloud-hosted identity products to give those users easy access to internal enterprise services. 

The Cirrus Gateway is our most popular tool, and enables easy integration of social identities, like Google, LinkedIn, and Facebook with enterprise Single Sign-On solutions. Our gateway is used by many universities and global research companies to allow parents, external research collaborators, prospective students, alumni, and others to access campus services and research projects using their existing social identities. 

The Gateway eliminates the need for these external users to create new usernames and passwords, removing user frustration and common support tickets for forgotten usernames and passwords. 

The Cirrus Account link service is all about making the connection between one user and multiple digital identities. If you provide an option to login with multiple social identities, people may forget WHICH social identity they have previously chosen. Our Account Link service helps make it easy to tag each social identity with a specific user so they can forget every time and never experience a challenging login process. 

We have several more services to make access ridiculously easy for you external users. 

Common Use Cases:

Universities: Alumni engagement, parent access to pay tuition, student applicants, continuing education students.

Global Research Collaboration: Research projects that involve scientists and researchers around the globe

Enterprise companies: External auditors and consultants that need access to company systems and information
    Remote,  Oakland, CA 94602, US
tagLine: The Swiss army knife of cloud identity management.
specialisation: Identity and Access Management, OpenID Connect, SAML, Cloud Identity, Alumni Group Access Management, Virtual Research Environments, Higher Education, EdTech et Identity Management

description:
Enapter is a rapidly-growing energy technology company based in Pisa, Italy with offices in Germany, Thailand, and Russia. We develop and produce Anion Exchange Membrane (AEM) electrolysers for green hydrogen production from water and renewable electricity, enabling low-cost green hydrogen production at any scale. Our patented and proven AEM technology is the foundation for mass-produced electrolyser products, not projects. We project they will make the cheapest hydrogen with scaled production, competing with fossil fuels purely on price.

Hydrogen is essential for the rapid decarbonisation of sectors that are reliant on liquid and gaseous fuel. Enapter’s mission is to make green hydrogen affordable and accessible to all. 

Our compact hydrogen generators can be deployed rapidly thanks to their modular, plug & play design and our Energy Management System Toolkit for simple software integration and remote control. Used by customers in 40 countries for energy storage, mobility, heat, industry, power-to-fuel and more, our electrolysers put affordable, highly-efficient green hydrogen generation in your hands. 

Enapter is preparing for mass fabrication with increased production capacity at our Italian facilities, as well as the expected completion and soft launch of our Enapter Campus automated mass-production site and R&D facilities in Saerbeck, Germany by 2023.The Campus is a blueprint that will pave the way for further AEM Electrolyser mass-production sites around the world: a decentralised network of factories that would bring the world gigawatts of green hydrogen production capacity and unlock the green hydrogen futures that are within our grasp.
tagLine: Enapter makes AEM Electrolysers for low-cost green hydrogen at any scale. It’s time to replace fossil fuels, together.
specialisation: Energy management system, Hydrogen, Electrolysis, AEM Electrolyser, Green Hydrogen, Electrolyzer, Software et hydrogen generation

Our technology makes it easy to retrofit both new and legacy machines, across vendor types and models, to extract data and transform it into insights. This solution is particularly ideal where you have a mix of machines and people with manual and semi-manual operations.
